<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Befb have you ever considered that your source might be a little BIASED and might tell his side to make himself look better?  <br>
<br>
If this Nag thing was such a huge deal then why hasn't the PO guildmaster posted anywhere on the board himself?<br>
<br>
<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Yup, I'm the &quot;source&quot; and hell yeah, I'm a little bit biased.  Thanks for pointing that out.  <br>
<br>
For those who don't know, I'm the guild leader of the Promethian Order and I love my guild.  So I'm about as biased on this issue as say.... a member of Sacred Fires.  But actualy, there are really only 3 people that know what happened.  Carrais, Sotae, and myself.<br>
<br>
Rather than rant about it, let me just post a sequence of events.<br>
<br>
Tuesday night, we were aware that SF was killing Naggy.  I was chatting off and on with Sotae, wished them luck, wanted to know how the were doing, etc...  I'll admit it, I'm just a nOOb and dragon raids, even someone elses, excite me still (shrug).  After it was over I sent him my congrats.  He told me they were leaving to kill Vox.  I said hey... we have Vox scheduled this week.  He then told me about the emergency patch.<br>
<br>
Yes, we found out about the emergency patch from a member of SF.<br>
<br>
<br>
Great, I said, in that case we'll go kill Naggy tomorow.  Two minutes pass.  Sotae sends me another tell saying &quot;actualy, we're gonna kill him again tomorrow&quot;. <br>
<br>
Yes, they planned to kill naggy Tuesday night, go kill Vox tuseday night, and turn around and kill Nagster again on Wednesday.  And yes, for those of you that are nitpicking, I announced our intent to kill Naggy first.<br>
<br>
So anyhow, I sent him a tell back saying &quot;hey, you killed naggy tonight and are on your way to kill Vox, let us have a turn tomorrow&quot;.  No response.  So we posted the plan here on the event calendar.<br>
<br>
I think it would be fair to say that the spawn was contested all the way back on tuesday night.  The fact that we posted to the calendar first isn't all the meaningfull IMHO.    Yes, we posted first, and yes, we told them we would like to kill naggy on wednesday before they mentioned it to us but it's not a huge deal.  We want to kill naggy and vox for one reason only, epic components.  And from what I've been told, Naggy didn't drop the paladin book anyhow.<br>
<br>
Here's what bothers me.<br>
<br>
On wednesday morning Sacred Fires began gathering to kill Nagafen.  I sent Sotae a tell, asking what the heck was going on.  I sent the tell to Sotae because he's the one person in the guild I've had any real contact with lately and because he's the one I'd been chatting with the previous night.  He didn't respond.  I sent him two more tells.  Finaly Carrais sent me a tell.  In the conversation that ensued, he told me Dragons can't be scheduled.  <br>
<br>
Dragons can't be scheduled?  I refer you to the calendar on this board where SF has scheduled dragon raids.<br>
<br>
I protested.  I warned him that he was hurting relations between our guilds.  He told me that my guild had a reputation for hurting people and hoped that we would grow out of it.  Told me to cry him a river and grow up.  Told me I was an idiot for thinking dragons could be scheduled.  Told me Nagafen had been up for 8 hours already and it's first come first serve.  Told me if we didn't hurry up and move on Vox they were going to kill her too.  (our plan is still to kill Vox on friday btw).  <br>
<br>
Realizing that nothing I could say was going to change his mind I wished him luck on Nagafen and in the future and attempted to end the conversation.  Each time he persisted, saying something else mildly insulting about me or my guild.  <br>
<br>
My feeling is this.  There are some nice people in SF.  Those that treat me and my guild with courtesy and respect can continue to expect the same in return.  Those that choose discourtesy and disrespect can expect us to turn our backs and walk away.   As a whole, I've washed my hands of Sacred Fires.  Good luck to you in your future endeavors.  For any guild leaders that wish to cooperate when it comes to scheduling, feel free to seek me out, here, in game, or on our message boards.<br>
<br>
Keadaian Songborne<br>
Iksar Warrior of 48 seasons<br>
Guild Leader,<br>
